Equity Bank of Kenya Retains About $50 Million to Fund Expansion, CEO Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-30T09:18:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/equity-bank-of-kenya-retains-about-50-million-to-fund-expansion-ceo-says.html
Equity Bank Ltd. (EQBNK) ,  Kenya ’s biggest
lender by market value, retained 4 billion shillings ($47.8
million) of its earnings to fund the company’s expansion, Chief
Executive Officer James Mwangi said.  Equity plans to open branches in neighboring Tanzania and
 Rwanda  this year, Mwangi said at a meeting of shareholders today
in Nairobi, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  